This is a newer LA Fitness and located on the corner of University & Stapley.
I regularly go to 6 different LA Fitnesses each week and this is the best of all of them.
The machines are top of the line with an entire row + of treadmills.
Each has a digital readout and a television if you want to watch while running.
The spin room is amazing with the instructor on the floor and multiple rows of bikes in a stadium seating layout.
I go for the Tuesday 5:45 zumba with Scheyla.
Get there early because the room gets filled to capacity each week.

Pros: spacious, state of the art equipment, multiple pieces of common equipment, clean work out floor, clean locker rooms, affordable Cons: single story, no "big tire", no kettlebell weights, cold room temp Overall a great gym for the price, just wish they had a tire and kettlebell weights.

